    <h2 id="HTML Colors">HTML Colors</h2>
      <p>Colors are specified using predefined color names, or <b>RGB, HEX, HSL, RGBA, HSLA</b> values.</p>
      <p>For a full list of color names, see: <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/colors/colors_names.asp"> 140 HTML Color Names</a></p>
      <h3 style="background-color:Tomato;">Color Names</h3>
      <h3 style="background-color:MediumSeaGreen;">Background Color</h3>
      <h3 style="color:DodgerBlue;">Text Color</h3>
      <h3 style="border:2px solid Violet;">Border Color</h3>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">Color Values</h3>
      <p style="background-color:rgb(255, 99, 71);">rgb(255, 99, 71)</p>
      <p style="background-color:#ff6347;">#ff6347</p>
      <p style="background-color:hsl(9, 100%, 64%);">hsl(9, 100%, 64%)</p>
      
      <p style="background-color:rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.5);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.5)</p>
      <p style="background-color:hsla(9, 100%, 64%, 0.5);">hsla(9, 100%, 64%, 0.5)</p>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">RGB Color Values</h3>
        <p><strong>rgb(red, green, blue)</strong></p>
        <p>Each parameter (red, green, and blue) defines the intensity of the color with a value between 0 and 255.</p>

        <p>This means that there are <b>256 x 256 x 256 = 16777216</b> possible colors!</p>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">Shades of Gray</h3>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(60, 60, 60);">rgb(60, 60, 60)#404040</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(100, 100, 100);">rgb(100, 100, 100)#686868</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(140, 140, 140);">rgb(140, 140, 140)#a0a0a0</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(180, 180, 180);">rgb(180, 180, 180)#bebebe</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(200, 200, 200);">rgb(200, 200, 200)#dcdcdc</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgb(240, 240, 240);">rgb(240, 240, 240)#f8f8f8</h1>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">RGBA Color Values</h3>
         <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 0);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0)</h1>
         <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 0.2);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.2)</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 0.4);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.4)</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 0.6);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.6)</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 0.8);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.8)</h1>
          <h1 style="background-color:rgba(124, 164, 71, 1);">rgba(255, 99, 71, 1)</h1>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">HEX Color Values</h3>
        <p>In HTML, a color can be specified using a hexadecimal value in the form:</p>
        <p><strong>#rrggbb</strong></p>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">HSL Color Values</h3>
        <p><strong>hsl(hue, saturation, lightness)</strong></p>
        <p>Hue is a degree on the color wheel (from 0 to 360). 0 - red, 120 - green, 240 - blue.</p>
        <p>Saturation is a percentage value,can be described as the intensity of a color.; 0% means a shade of gray and 100% is the full color.</p>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 50%);">hsl(0, 100%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 80%, 50%);">hsl(0, 80%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 60%, 50%);">hsl(0, 60%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 40%, 50%);">hsl(0, 40%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 20%, 50%);">hsl(0, 20%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 0%, 50%);">hsl(0, 0%, 50%)</h1>
        <p>Lightness is also a percentage; 0% is black, 100% is white.</p>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 0%);">hsl(0, 100%, 0%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 25%);">hsl(0, 100%, 25%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 50%);">hsl(0, 100%, 50%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 75%);">hsl(0, 100%, 75%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 90%);">hsl(0, 100%, 90%)</h1>
           <h1 style="background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 100%);">hsl(0, 100%, 100%)</h1>
      <h3 style="color:SlateBlue;background-color:LightGray;">HSLA Color Values</h3>
        <p><strong>hsla(hue, saturation, lightness, alpha)</strong></p>
    </section>
    
