      <h2 id="HTML Images">HTML Images </h2>
        <h3>HTML Images Syntax</h3>
        <p>The HTML<b>"img" </b> tag is used to embed an image in a Web page.</p>
        <p>Images are not technically inserted into a Web page; images are linked to Web pages.</p>
        <p>The <b>"img" </b>tag creates a holding space for the referenced image.</p>
        <p>The <b>"src"</b> attribute is required, and it specifies the path to the image you want to display.</p>
        <p>The <b>"alt"</b> attribute holds a text description of the image, which isn't mandatory but is incredibly useful for accessibility.</p>
        <p>The <b>"width" and "height"</b> attributes are optional, and they specify the width and height of the image.</p>
        <p>Use the <b>"style" </b>attribute to apply CSS styles to images.</p>
        <p> <strong>< img src="url" alt="alternatetext" ></strong></p>
        <h3>Image Size - Width and Height</h3>
